<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Soccer Roundup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILAN, Italy (AP) -- Maurizio Ganz scored with seconds remaining  
on a shot that deflected off the hand of defender Marcello 
Castellini, giving AC Milan a 3-2 victory over Sampdoria of Genoa 
on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	With three games remaining, AC Milan (17-4-10) remained one  
point behind Lazio of Rome (18-5-8), won 3-0 at Udinese on goals by 
Sinisa Mihajlovic, Christian Vieri and Roberto Mancini. 
</P>
<P>
	AC Milan, in search of its fifth title of the 1990s, plays at  
Juventus of Turin next week, when Lazio is host to Bologna. Lazio's 
lone league championship came in 1974. 
</P>
<P>
	AC Milan stretched its unbeaten streak to eight, but not before  
struggling all afternoon against a Sampdoria side that is 17th in 
the 18-team league and played the entire second half a man short. 
</P>
<P>
	AC Milan went ahead in the 17th minute on Massimo Ambrosini's  
25-yard shot, his first goal since November 1997. Sampdoria 
defender Saliou Lassissi was ejected at the end of the first half 
for fouling Ganz, but Sampdoria (7-15-9) tied it in the 59th on 
Vincenzo Montella's header off a corner kick. 
</P>
<P>
	Leonardo put AC Milan back ahead on a 20-yard free kick with 12  
minutes to go, but Marco Franceschetti's first goal of the season 
tied the score with four minutes remaining. The winning goal came 
in the fifth minute of injury time. 
</P>
<P>
	At Udine, Mihajlovic converted a penalty kick in the 29th after  
Mancini was fouled by Valerio Bertotto. Vieri (48th minute) and 
Mancini (57th) added goals on headers. The win was Lazio's 
team-record eighth on the road this season. 
</P>
<P>
	In other games, Fiorentina routed Perugia 5-1, Parma edged  
last-place Empoli 1-0, Salernitana upset Juventus 1-0; Bari beat 
Piacenza 3-1, Cagliari topped Bologna 3-1 and Vicenza beat Venezia 
2-1. Internazionale of Milan's game at AS Roma was pushed back to 
Monday because of a papal beatification. 
</P>
</TEXT>
