<HEADLINE> Pfeiffer Makes 'People' List Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Michelle Pfeiffer, who has just made People  
magazine's ``50 Most Beautiful'' list for the sixth time, says she 
would like to have longer legs and curls. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm not unhappy with the way I look now,'' Pfeiffer, 41, says  
in the May 10 issue of People magazine. But ``I really would like 
curls.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The movie star is featured on the cover of the magazine's  
special issue, making her the only celebrity to have graced the 
``50 Most Beautiful'' cover twice. 
</P>
<P>
	And Pfeiffer has outdone lookers like Tom Cruise, John F.  
Kennedy Jr., and Mel Gibson -- who have 'only' been on the list five 
times. They were not on it this year. 
</P>
<P>
	Jennifer Aniston, Benjamin Bratt, and Nicole Kidman are also on  
this years list. 
</P>
<P>
	``A person's looks are a double-edged sword. Sometimes it works  
in your favor, sometimes it works against you,'' Pfeiffer said. 
``All I really care about is that I'm able to age gracefully and 
that I don't ever look like a wax figure of myself.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Pfeiffer, the mother of two children, is married to producer  
David E. Kelley, whose credits include ``The Practice'' and ``Ally 
McBeal.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
