<HEADLINE> Graham To Lead Prayer at Indy 500 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- The Rev. Billy Graham has been chosen to  
give the invocation at the Indianapolis 500 on May 30. 
</P>
<P>
	Tony George, president of the Indianapolis Motor Speedway,  
personally invited Graham to give the invocation. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm honored to be invited,'' Graham said Saturday. ``I have  
never been there for the 500. I have flown over the Speedway when 
it was on several times. But to be there and to give the prayer 
will be a great honor for me.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The evangelist will preach for four nights starting June 3  
during his Indianapolis crusade. Organizers expect 200,000 people 
to attend the Christian revival. 
</P>
<P>
	Graham's prayer will break a 25-year tradition at the race.  
Since 1974, the invocation has been given by the Catholic 
archbishop of Indianapolis. 
