<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Elway Gets Towed Before Retirement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ENGLEWOOD, Colo. (AP) -- Forget about the famed fourth-quarter  
comebacks, the two Super Bowl rings and the sure induction to the 
NFL Hall of Fame. What John Elway really needed Saturday night was 
a parking pass. 
</P>
<P>
	Elway provided comic relief at his emotional retirement ceremony  
Sunday when he recounted having his car towed after dinner with 
several teammates in downtown Denver. 
</P>
<P>
	``The sign didn't say `No parking.' It said, `Postal customers  
only,''' Elway recalled. ``It's 9 o'clock at night and there's 
other cars parked in there. I said, `This must be OK.''' 
</P>
<P>
	Wrong.  
</P>
<P>
	``He came out and believe it or not, they towed his car -- the  
King's car,'' Broncos owner Pat Bowlen said. 
</P>
<P>
	As he has done so many times on the football field, Elway  
improvised. He found out that the towing company was near Coors 
Field a few miles away, and he set out to find a taxi. 
</P>
<P>
	``I start walking. If I run into a cab, I run into a cab,''  
Elway said. ``What do I run into? I run into six limos of high 
school students on their prom. Needless to say, I got to the tow 
lot. It was about a three-mile walk.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The driver of the tow truck recognized his victim immediately.  
</P>
<P>
	``We figured it was a brand new car, we figured it was somebody  
with money, but we didn't think it was going to be you,'' the 
driver told Elway. 
</P>
<P>
	The woman collecting the towing fee wasn't so impressed.  
</P>
<P>
	``When he got there, a lady said, `Can I see some ID, please?  
And I need $100 dollars,''' Bowlen said. ``Welcome to the world of 
the retired great quarterbacks, John.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Towing companies aside, Elway repeatedly thanked the fans of  
Denver and Colorado for their support during his 16-year career 
with the Broncos. 
</P>
<P>
	``Denver has been great. Colorado has been great to me and my  
family -- kind of took us under their wing,'' he said. ``We couldn't 
have asked for anything better.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
