<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 7 Dead in Church Bus Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MAYHILL, N.M. (AP) -- A camper being towed by a pickup truck  
broke loose Sunday and hit a bus and rammed into another pickup, 
killing six girls traveling home by bus from a church retreat and 
the driver of the second pickup, state police said. 
</P>
<P>
	When the pickup swerved, the camper broke loose and its fifth  
wheel, a device that mounts it to the pickup's bed, broke free and 
``tore along the side of bus,'' state police Capt. John Balderston 
said. It also struck the second pickup, which was behind the bus. 
</P>
<P>
	The mounting device ``just slid and just smashed into the bus,''  
said Julie Selleck, who works at Pine Springs Summer Camp. ``It's 
pretty devastating.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The girls, ages 12 to 17, were killed instantly, Balderston  
said. There was no information available about the pickup driver 
who was killed. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to those killed, three people were in critical  
condition, five were in serious condition and 19 were in stable 
condition at Alamogordo and Albuquerque hospitals, Selleck said. 
</P>
<P>
	About 80 people from Green Lawn Church of Christ in Lubbock,  
Texas, had been at the isolated, mountainous camp in the Lincoln 
National Forest for a weekend retreat, Selleck said. 
</P>
<P>
	Members of the church group gathered after the accident at Cuba  
Avenue Church of Christ in Alamogordo. They were to take a bus 
provided by Holloman Air Force Base to another church in Artesia 
and home from there, church elder Jim Morrow said. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's a a lot of togetherness,'' Morrow said. ``We had a  
special prayer service tonight. It was emotional and intense.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Mayhill is about 150 miles southeast of Albuquerque.  
</P>
</TEXT>
