<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 7 Dead in Church Bus Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MAYHILL, N.M. (AP) -- A spare tire apparently fell Sunday from a  
truck and smashed into a bus ferrying students from a church camp 
to their homes in Texas, killing seven people, state police said. 
</P>
<P>
	``It just slid and just smashed into the bus,'' said Julie  
Selleck, who works at Pine Springs Summer Camp. ``It's pretty 
devastating.'' 
</P>
<P>
	About 80 people from Green Lawn Church of Christ in Lubbock,  
Texas, had been at the isolated, mountainous camp in the Lincoln 
National Forest for a weekend retreat, Selleck said. 
</P>
<P>
	The 2 p.m. crash on U.S. 82 involved reportedly a semi-trailer,  
a motor home and the church bus, but that was not immediately 
confirmed, state police spokesman Robert Smoot said. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to those killed, one person was in critical  
condition, five were in serious condition and 19 were in stable 
condition at a Alamogordo and Albuquerque hospitals, Selleck said. 
</P>
<P>
	Mayhill is about 150 miles southeast of Albuquerque.  
