<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 7 Dead in Church Bus Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MAYHILL, N.M. (AP) -- A spare tire apparently fell from a truck  
Sunday and smashed into a bus carrying students from a church camp 
to their homes in Texas, killing seven people, state police said. 
Six of the dead were girls from the church camp. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's pretty devastating,'' said Julie Selleck, who works at  
Pine Springs Summer Camp. 
</P>
<P>
	About 80 people from Green Lawn Church of Christ in Lubbock,  
Texas, had been at the isolated, mountainous camp in the Lincoln 
National Forest for a weekend retreat, Selleck said. 
</P>
<P>
	The 2 p.m. crash on U.S. 82 reportedly involved a semi-trailer,  
a motor home and the church bus, but that could not be confirmed, 
state police spokesman Robert Smoot said. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to those killed, three people was in critical  
condition, five were in serious condition and 19 were in stable 
condition at hospitals in Alamogordo and Albuquerque, Selleck said. 
</P>
<P>
	Members of the Green Lawn church group gathered after the  
accident at Cuba Avenue Church of Christ in Alamogordo. They were 
to take a bus provided by Holloman Air Force Base to another church 
in Artesia and home from there, church elder Jim Morrow said. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's a a lot of togetherness,'' Morrow said. ``We had a  
special prayer service tonight. It was emotional and intense.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Mayhill is about 150 miles southeast of Albuquerque.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
